==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Spangle
<hw>Span"gle</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[OE.
<ets>spangel</ets>, dim. of AS. <ets>spange</ets>. See <er>Spang</er> a
spangle.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A small plate or boss of shining metal;
something brilliant used as an ornament, especially when stitched on the
dress.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Figuratively, any little thing that sparkless.</def>
⟦ldquo⟧The rich <xex>spangles</xex> that adorn the sky.⟦rdquo⟧
<rj><au>Waller.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Oak spangle</b></col>. <cd>See under
<er>Oak</er>.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Spangle</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Spangle
<hw>Span"gle</hw>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p. p.</pos>
<conjf>Spangled</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos>
<conjf>Spangling</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>.]</vmorph> <def>To set or sprinkle
with, or as with, spangles; to adorn with small, distinct, brilliant
bodies; <as>as, a <ex>spangled</ex> breastplate</as>.</def>
<rj><au>Donne.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>What stars do <qex>spangle</qex> heaven with such beauty?</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Spangled coquette</b></col> <fld>(Zool.)</fld>, <cd>a
tropical humming bird (<spn>Lophornis reginae</spn>). See
<er>Coquette</er>, 2.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Spangle</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 3 ====
HEADWORD: Spangle
<hw>Span"gle</hw>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <def>To show brilliant spots or
points; to glisten; to glitter.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Some men by feigning words as dark as mine⟦br⟧
Make truth to <qex>spangle</qex>, and its rays to shine.</q>
<rj><qau>Bunyan.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Spangler</ent>⟦br⟧
